data.title: Blue plaque for Charles Worth at Bourne, Lincolnshire
data.meta_description: A prestigious blue plaque issued by English Heritage can be seen on the front of Wake House in North Street to mark the birth of Charles Worth (1825-95), son of a local solicitor, who left to seek a career in Paris where he achieved fame as a fashion designer and became the father of haute couture.
